1
00:00:00,680 --> 00:00:02,430
Previously on Fairy Tail:

2
00:00:02,690 --> 00:00:07,490
We finally defeated the commander 
of Oracion Seis, Brain!

3
00:00:07,490 --> 00:00:09,850
That dude Jura's crazy powerful!

4
00:00:09,850 --> 00:00:12,070
But Nirvana isn't stopping...

5
00:00:12,320 --> 00:00:13,740
And we don't even know how to stop it!

6
00:00:13,740 --> 00:00:14,790
What'll we do?

7
00:00:14,790 --> 00:00:16,500
We will never give in.

8
00:00:16,500 --> 00:00:18,630
For our hopes are already as one!

9
00:01:52,420 --> 00:01:59,320
This is the guild which Wendy and 
Carla are members of, Caitshelter.

10
00:02:05,800 --> 00:02:07,700
Everyone, we've got a big problem!

11
00:02:07,700 --> 00:02:08,840
It's Nirvana!

12
00:02:08,840 --> 00:02:10,820
Nirvana is heading this way!

13
00:02:10,820 --> 00:02:11,570
What?

14
00:02:11,570 --> 00:02:14,180
The alliance plan failed?

15
00:02:14,180 --> 00:02:16,610
Even with Jura and Erza with them?

16
00:02:16,610 --> 00:02:17,980
Master!

17
00:02:18,720 --> 00:02:20,850
Nabula...

18
00:02:27,840 --> 00:02:30,150
Don't pour if you're gonna 
drink straight from the bottle!

19
00:02:30,150 --> 00:02:31,970
Nabula...

20
00:02:31,970 --> 00:02:34,230
Listen, Nirvana is heading here...

21
00:02:34,250 --> 00:02:37,310
What? For truth?

22
00:02:38,830 --> 00:02:41,270
Swallow first, <i>then</i> talk!

23
00:02:42,320 --> 00:02:45,590
Nirvana is heading this way?

24
00:02:46,210 --> 00:02:49,810
Is this fate? Or merely coincidence-nabula?

25
00:02:50,490 --> 00:02:53,280
I hope that Wendy is safe...

26
00:02:53,280 --> 00:02:54,000
Yeah.

27
00:02:54,250 --> 00:02:57,030
We're not actually any help in a pinch.

28
00:03:01,240 --> 00:03:03,030
Swallow, <i>then</i> talk!

29
00:03:04,100 --> 00:03:06,910
The power of the magic of light still lives!

30
00:03:08,070 --> 00:03:12,780
Nabula! It shines brightly!

31
00:03:14,210 --> 00:03:17,240
But, this is no coincidence...

32
00:03:17,490 --> 00:03:20,640
There's someone who knows our real identity.

33
00:03:20,640 --> 00:03:22,340
That must be why they're aiming for here.

34
00:03:22,790 --> 00:03:25,110
Nabula...

35
00:03:25,110 --> 00:03:28,870
We've been together for who knows how long, 
and I still don't know what "nabula" means.

36
00:03:33,750 --> 00:03:36,160
Master, let's evacuate!

37
00:03:36,160 --> 00:03:39,060
Our barrier can't protect against Nirvana!

38
00:03:40,260 --> 00:03:42,680
You fools!

39
00:03:45,400 --> 00:03:50,290
There are people who are fighting-nabula, 
and trying to stop it!

40
00:03:50,290 --> 00:03:54,800
For those who believe in victory, 
there is no need to move!

41
00:04:02,660 --> 00:04:04,480
So I say...

42
00:04:04,770 --> 00:04:07,790
But perhaps the time has come.

43
00:04:09,700 --> 00:04:15,250
The time for us to pay for our crimes.

44
00:04:18,480 --> 00:04:20,530
It is Your Words.

45
00:04:42,630 --> 00:04:44,420
Stop it?

46
00:04:44,420 --> 00:04:47,180
But we don't know <i>how</i> to stop it!

47
00:04:47,430 --> 00:04:48,620
Like, breaking it?

48
00:04:48,620 --> 00:04:50,870
Yup, figures you'd think like that.

49
00:04:50,870 --> 00:04:54,120
How do you plan on breaking 
something this huge?

50
00:04:56,890 --> 00:05:00,630
It would be faster to ask Brain.

51
00:05:00,630 --> 00:05:03,060
Will he tell us just like that, I wonder?

52
00:05:03,800 --> 00:05:06,150
Maybe Jellal would know...

53
00:05:11,140 --> 00:05:12,470
Did you say something?

54
00:05:12,470 --> 00:05:13,940
Is something the matter?

55
00:05:13,940 --> 00:05:15,930
No, it's nothing.

56
00:05:16,190 --> 00:05:19,660
I think I might be on to something. 
I want to check it out.

57
00:05:20,280 --> 00:05:22,350
Wendy, wait!

58
00:05:22,350 --> 00:05:23,420
Hey!

59
00:05:23,970 --> 00:05:25,540
What's with her?

60
00:05:26,890 --> 00:05:29,720
Everyone, can you hear me?

61
00:05:30,040 --> 00:05:33,110
It is me, Hot Eye.

62
00:05:33,110 --> 00:05:35,140
Mass telepathy?

63
00:05:35,140 --> 00:05:35,930
Who is it?

64
00:05:35,930 --> 00:05:38,330
It is Richard-dono! You are unharmed?

65
00:05:38,330 --> 00:05:41,670
Unfortunately, I am injured.

66
00:05:41,670 --> 00:05:44,690
I was no match for Midnight, as I feared.

67
00:05:44,940 --> 00:05:50,240
Everyone, please work 
together to defeat Midnight!

68
00:05:50,240 --> 00:05:55,010
If you defeat him, Nirvana's supply 
of magical power will be cut off,

69
00:05:55,010 --> 00:05:57,290
and the city should come to a halt.

70
00:05:57,290 --> 00:05:58,730
Who is it?

71
00:05:58,730 --> 00:06:01,380
So, it moves using Body Link magic...

72
00:06:04,050 --> 00:06:07,070
He is directly below the King's Summit.

73
00:06:07,070 --> 00:06:11,720
Be careful. He is very, very powerful!

74
00:06:11,990 --> 00:06:13,370
Richard-dono...

75
00:06:13,370 --> 00:06:14,640
Directly below us?

76
00:06:14,640 --> 00:06:17,210
Okay! I can see the light 
at the end of the tunnel!

77
00:06:17,210 --> 00:06:19,030
Powerful, huh?

78
00:06:19,300 --> 00:06:20,980
I'm getting fired up!

79
00:06:20,980 --> 00:06:23,310
Natsu... It's to stop this thing, remember?

80
00:06:23,310 --> 00:06:25,630
Right! Let's go!

81
00:06:25,630 --> 00:06:29,040
Of the six prayers, only one is left.

82
00:06:29,510 --> 00:06:31,650
I believe in everyone!

83
00:06:32,360 --> 00:06:37,200
You will surely win, and 
be able to stop Nirvana!

84
00:06:38,440 --> 00:06:41,880
Please...

85
00:06:44,390 --> 00:06:45,710
Richard-dono!

86
00:06:48,910 --> 00:06:51,090
You won't get away with this...

87
00:06:51,620 --> 00:06:53,480
You'll pay...

88
00:06:53,480 --> 00:06:54,710
There?

89
00:06:54,710 --> 00:06:56,070
Okay!

90
00:06:58,310 --> 00:07:01,280
Show yourself, you drowsy bastard!

91
00:07:05,370 --> 00:07:06,940
It's a trap!

92
00:07:12,380 --> 00:07:13,840
What was that explosion?

93
00:07:14,480 --> 00:07:15,910
It was toward the King's Summit...

94
00:07:16,510 --> 00:07:22,810
Father is such a bad person, 
taking away all my fun.

95
00:07:28,930 --> 00:07:32,220
You two are now the final prey.

96
00:07:32,810 --> 00:07:34,840
I <i>do</i> hope this will be entertaining.

97
00:07:38,760 --> 00:07:40,800
Stand back, Erza.

98
00:07:41,200 --> 00:07:42,440
Jellal...

99
00:08:01,140 --> 00:08:03,370
Damn it... That hurt.

100
00:08:04,320 --> 00:08:07,040
Is everyone alive?

101
00:08:07,040 --> 00:08:08,250
Aye...

102
00:08:08,250 --> 00:08:13,100
What happened? We were caught up 
in that giant explosion and...

103
00:08:13,860 --> 00:08:16,300
We're buried?

104
00:08:16,860 --> 00:08:18,510
Wait, this is...

105
00:08:31,220 --> 00:08:32,160
Old dude!

106
00:08:32,160 --> 00:08:33,240
Jura!

107
00:08:33,240 --> 00:08:35,290
He protected us?

108
00:08:44,020 --> 00:08:45,460
Gramps!

109
00:08:47,490 --> 00:08:51,000
Stay well, young ones...

110
00:08:51,800 --> 00:08:56,070
I am glad you are safe.

111
00:08:58,690 --> 00:08:59,510
Old dude!

112
00:08:59,510 --> 00:09:00,760
Hang in there!

113
00:09:00,760 --> 00:09:02,280
Jura!

114
00:09:02,510 --> 00:09:05,270
Damn it all!

115
00:09:09,300 --> 00:09:11,950
It's definitely heading toward Caitshelter.

116
00:09:13,220 --> 00:09:17,230
Wendy, I'm sorry, but I 
can't fly much farther.

117
00:09:17,580 --> 00:09:19,740
Okay. Sorry, Carla.

118
00:09:19,740 --> 00:09:22,220
Let's search for Jellal on foot.

119
00:09:22,220 --> 00:09:24,250
You have a good sense of smell, after all.

120
00:09:32,080 --> 00:09:37,580
But that Jellal smells a little 
different than the one I know.

121
00:09:37,980 --> 00:09:41,050
A-Anyway, let's search for Jellal.

122
00:09:42,390 --> 00:09:45,360
He might be able to stop this thing.

123
00:09:45,360 --> 00:09:45,890
Right.

124
00:09:48,440 --> 00:09:50,640
Please be safe, Jellal...

125
00:09:50,960 --> 00:10:01,120
It seems like you forgot about me, but I 
haven't forgotten about you for a single day.

126
00:10:17,700 --> 00:10:19,450
It didn't hit?

127
00:10:27,060 --> 00:10:28,890
Stop it, Jellal...

128
00:10:28,890 --> 00:10:30,520
It's impossible for you 
with your body like that.

129
00:10:31,000 --> 00:10:31,690
I will...

130
00:10:36,420 --> 00:10:37,320
Come here.

131
00:11:14,830 --> 00:11:19,280
Pitiful... This is that Jellal?

132
00:11:26,840 --> 00:11:28,950
Just a pathetic clown.

133
00:11:54,310 --> 00:12:00,240
Did you forget how to use magic along 
with your memories, Jellal-kun?

134
00:12:06,070 --> 00:12:09,160
Someone like Jellal defeated so easily?

135
00:12:16,950 --> 00:12:19,960
Oh? Still alive?

136
00:12:20,800 --> 00:12:27,470
No... It's that he used up more magic power casting the 
self-destruction magic circle on himself than I had thought.

137
00:12:31,480 --> 00:12:36,280
I want to see you suffer in fear even more.

138
00:12:42,370 --> 00:12:45,950
Time for the main dish already, Erza Scarlet?

139
00:12:47,950 --> 00:12:49,120
My sword slash was deflected?

140
00:12:49,120 --> 00:12:52,040
Erza, stand back! This guy's dangerous!

141
00:12:56,500 --> 00:12:57,290
Again?

142
00:13:05,340 --> 00:13:06,420
What?

143
00:13:08,630 --> 00:13:09,790
Erza!

144
00:13:26,480 --> 00:13:27,490
I see...

145
00:13:28,700 --> 00:13:30,330
So that is your magic!

146
00:13:31,140 --> 00:13:36,410
Yes... My "Reflector" can 
warp and twist anything.

147
00:13:37,580 --> 00:13:44,210
It can reflect back magic, and using the 
bending of light, can even make illusions.

148
00:13:44,670 --> 00:13:46,420
What incredible magic...

149
00:13:50,660 --> 00:13:51,850
Here I come!

150
00:13:52,770 --> 00:13:54,640
Didn't you hear me?

151
00:13:55,410 --> 00:13:58,280
Magic cannot hit me!

152
00:14:02,770 --> 00:14:03,810
What'll we do?

153
00:14:03,810 --> 00:14:04,720
He's hurt bad!

154
00:14:04,720 --> 00:14:06,650
Don't die on us, dude!

155
00:14:07,750 --> 00:14:09,070
It was a trap...

156
00:14:13,730 --> 00:14:16,420
What a joke...

157
00:14:17,110 --> 00:14:24,000
Brain used up all the rest of his power 
and could only get rid of one of you.

158
00:14:24,000 --> 00:14:25,460
Who is it?

159
00:14:25,460 --> 00:14:26,600
Up there!

160
00:14:28,930 --> 00:14:30,970
Pitiful...

161
00:14:31,770 --> 00:14:34,440
He's a disgrace to the Six Generals.

162
00:14:36,410 --> 00:14:42,310
Well, as long as Midnight is 
here, we haven't been defeated.

163
00:14:44,720 --> 00:14:48,860
Perhaps I will clean up 
the rest of you fools.

164
00:14:48,860 --> 00:14:49,610
The...

165
00:14:49,610 --> 00:14:50,240
The...

166
00:14:50,240 --> 00:14:51,090
The...

167
00:14:51,320 --> 00:14:53,340
The staff is talking!

168
00:14:53,340 --> 00:14:56,490
You talk too, even though you're a cat.

169
00:14:56,490 --> 00:14:57,580
Aye...

170
00:15:07,350 --> 00:15:10,570
That's the staff that Brain had.

171
00:15:10,570 --> 00:15:12,050
What's going on?

172
00:15:16,680 --> 00:15:19,850
Hey-hey-hey-hey-hey-hey-
hey-hey-hey-hey-hey-now!

173
00:15:20,640 --> 00:15:23,560
Wait, we don't know what it is!

174
00:15:23,560 --> 00:15:25,980
Stop this big city, you rotted stick!

175
00:15:25,980 --> 00:15:28,190
R-Rotted stick? How rude!

176
00:15:28,190 --> 00:15:31,570
Stick I'll accept, but what 
do you mean rotted, huh?

177
00:15:32,390 --> 00:15:36,740
I am the seventh member of Oracion Seis.

178
00:15:36,740 --> 00:15:39,300
I have awakened from my slumber to defeat...

179
00:15:39,300 --> 00:15:41,710
I said stop this city!

180
00:15:42,460 --> 00:15:46,590
Huh? But Oracion Seis has 6 members.

181
00:15:46,590 --> 00:15:50,850
Professor Happy's Fairy Tail Lectures!

182
00:15:50,850 --> 00:15:51,840
That's right!

183
00:15:51,840 --> 00:15:54,160
There are six members, and 
thus "Six Wizard Generals".

184
00:15:54,160 --> 00:15:58,140
The name is read as "Oracion Seis".

185
00:15:58,400 --> 00:16:00,130
Huh? That is strange.

186
00:16:00,130 --> 00:16:04,510
See? There are supposed to be 
six, so what's with the seventh?

187
00:16:04,510 --> 00:16:09,120
And wait... Are we dropping the 
whole talking staff thing already?

188
00:16:09,500 --> 00:16:12,610
It's all so ridiculous I 
don't know where to start.

189
00:16:14,800 --> 00:16:17,570
You violent brat...

190
00:16:18,610 --> 00:16:22,560
Soon I'll be able to see 
the guild of those fools...

191
00:16:22,560 --> 00:16:26,080
I must clean up the trash without delay.

192
00:16:26,080 --> 00:16:28,210
You mean Caitshelter?

193
00:16:28,470 --> 00:16:34,090
Exactly! We will begin our 
destruction by crushing them!

194
00:16:38,360 --> 00:16:39,930
Dance, my blades!

195
00:16:44,730 --> 00:16:46,940
You think you can hit 
me through sheer number?

196
00:16:51,280 --> 00:16:55,290
I told you before that I 
could reflect attacks back.

197
00:16:57,360 --> 00:16:58,370
Erza!

198
00:17:06,710 --> 00:17:08,010
More...

199
00:17:08,490 --> 00:17:11,090
Show me even more suffering!

200
00:17:16,520 --> 00:17:19,200
Nothing is better than that 
expression on your face...

201
00:17:28,600 --> 00:17:30,180
Impressive, as I thought.

202
00:17:31,790 --> 00:17:32,680
But...

203
00:17:33,050 --> 00:17:34,700
Spiral Pain!

204
00:17:50,720 --> 00:17:51,950
Oh, no!

205
00:17:52,790 --> 00:17:54,290
Over already?

206
00:18:01,320 --> 00:18:02,440
So powerful...

207
00:18:02,440 --> 00:18:05,270
Please don't die yet, Erza.

208
00:18:05,900 --> 00:18:09,390
Entertain me until we get to Caitshelter.

209
00:18:10,270 --> 00:18:11,480
Caitshelter?

210
00:18:12,240 --> 00:18:14,810
Our first target.

211
00:18:15,530 --> 00:18:17,290
Why attack there?

212
00:18:18,420 --> 00:18:25,550
Because the clan who created Nirvana to 
stop the war far in the past is there.

213
00:18:26,090 --> 00:18:27,630
The Nirvit.

214
00:18:28,410 --> 00:18:33,290
But Nirvana was a far more dangerous 
magic than they predicted.

215
00:18:33,890 --> 00:18:38,850
So they sealed away the magic 
that they themselves created.

216
00:18:39,310 --> 00:18:41,520
Afraid it would be used for evil,

217
00:18:41,520 --> 00:18:46,290
they continued to protect the seal 
for decades, and then centuries.

218
00:18:47,410 --> 00:18:53,370
Caitshelter is a guild formed specifically 
by the descendants of the Nirvit.

219
00:18:55,720 --> 00:19:02,950
They have the power to seal Nirvana once 
again, that is why we must destroy them.

220
00:19:07,490 --> 00:19:11,270
Isn't it a waste to let this 
incredible power stay asleep?

221
00:19:12,860 --> 00:19:17,710
With this power, the world 
can be led toward chaos!

222
00:19:19,420 --> 00:19:21,740
This is also a warning to everyone.

223
00:19:22,140 --> 00:19:26,390
We'll force the Nirvit, who love 
being neutral, to go to war!

224
00:19:27,470 --> 00:19:33,220
With the power of Nirvana, we'll engulf their 
hearts in darkness, and make them kill each other!

225
00:19:33,220 --> 00:19:35,020
Doesn't it just give you the chills?

226
00:19:35,020 --> 00:19:36,190
You fiend!

227
00:19:40,980 --> 00:19:45,370
Stop acting like you're a good guy, Jellal...

228
00:19:47,480 --> 00:19:48,740
Your...

229
00:19:50,210 --> 00:19:52,910
Your soul is darkness itself, after all.

230
00:19:53,770 --> 00:19:57,590
You are a sinister, vicious man 
with blood on your hands...

231
00:19:58,450 --> 00:19:59,170
That's not true!

232
00:20:00,230 --> 00:20:01,920
Yes, it is.

233
00:20:02,140 --> 00:20:05,820
You forced children into slave labor.

234
00:20:05,820 --> 00:20:07,430
You killed your friends.

235
00:20:07,430 --> 00:20:09,760
You even tried to kill Erza.

236
00:20:15,850 --> 00:20:20,190
Do you know how many people 
you've caused to suffer?

237
00:20:20,940 --> 00:20:27,520
Do you know how many people you've 
frightened, threatened, and made cry?

238
00:20:34,750 --> 00:20:36,010
Jellal...

239
00:20:38,560 --> 00:20:40,670
Come here.

240
00:20:45,160 --> 00:20:46,350
Jellal...

241
00:20:47,510 --> 00:20:50,680
You're a perfect fit for 
the new Six Generals.

242
00:21:08,030 --> 00:21:09,410
I know...

243
00:21:12,730 --> 00:21:15,750
I know the light within Jellal...

244
00:21:20,500 --> 00:21:21,480
Erza...

245
00:21:31,190 --> 00:21:32,680
You can still stand?

246
00:21:37,000 --> 00:21:40,280
Live, and grab the future in front of you.

247
00:21:41,320 --> 00:21:46,320
It is your words that give me 
the courage, that are my light.

248
00:21:50,760 --> 00:21:53,870
Just as the rumors say, Erza...

249
00:21:55,070 --> 00:21:56,790
I'll take great satisfaction 
in destroying you!

250
00:22:01,740 --> 00:22:05,340
I will stop you and your foolish desire!

251
00:22:06,400 --> 00:22:07,630
Without fail.

252
00:23:55,730 --> 00:24:01,170
We're all beat up, and it's <i>now </i>
that the strongest enemy shows up?

253
00:24:01,170 --> 00:24:03,530
It's like they hit the reset button!

254
00:24:03,530 --> 00:24:06,150
Our battles before weren't a waste.

255
00:24:06,150 --> 00:24:09,760
And besides, if we beat this 
guy, it's finally over for real!

256
00:24:09,760 --> 00:24:12,360
Always overly optimistic, huh Natsu?

257
00:24:12,360 --> 00:24:13,980
Just call me a positive thinker!

258
00:24:14,240 --> 00:24:16,110
Next time: Zero!

259
00:24:16,510 --> 00:24:19,600
But what you said is true, Natsu.

260
00:24:19,600 --> 00:24:21,940
See? I said something good, right?

261
00:24:21,940 --> 00:24:22,350
Right?

262
00:24:23,230 --> 00:24:24,570
And now you ruined it.

